<task id="R3-093" project="spaarke-platform-foundations-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Edge perf hint (non-referencing edge advisory)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completion-date>2026-06-21</completion-date>
    <completion-notes>
      Added 'edge-no-data-dependency' rule (warning severity) to canvasValidation.ts.
      Per-edge iteration loop added as a SIBLING to the per-NODE-type loop and 091's
      collision-check call, with a clear "Per-edge advisory rules (task 093)" comment
      marking the boundary for future maintainers. Sibling 091 had pre-coordinated by
      leaving a placeholder comment at the exact insertion point.

      Reused existing scanners: parseDownstreamNode for templateRef enumeration (covers
      configJson.fieldMappings, legacy fields dict, template/body/subject/description,
      and node.data template/emailBody/emailSubject) — no new regex, no new scanner.
      Skips when source has no outputVariable or target can't be parsed (graceful).
      Warning attaches to the source nodeId so the existing NodeValidationBadge
      surface (consumed by NodePropertiesForm) picks it up via the badge's existing
      `warnings` prop.

      Extended PlaybookNodeData with optional `warnings?: string[]` field (paired with
      existing `validationErrors?: string[]`) and updated NodePropertiesForm to pass
      `warnings={node.data.warnings ?? []}` to NodeValidationBadge. NO new badge
      component, NO new validation framework, NO new warning category — extension only.

      Save-not-blocked verification: confirmed playbookNodeSync.ts:294 uses
      hasValidationErrors(...) which filters severity === 'error'; warnings flow
      through to the result without blocking sync. My rule emits severity: 'warning'
      so save is never blocked. (Per FR-3H2.3 binding constraint.)

      §5 bridge gap (canvasStore → node.data.warnings) is a shared follow-up across
      091/092/093 per task 090 research §5 recommendation (a) — not addressed in 093
      to keep change scoped. Once the bridge lands (canvasStore subscribes to
      validatePromptSchemaNodes + groupValidationsByNode and patches node.data),
      this rule's warnings will surface in the badge popover automatically.

      Coordination with sibling 091: 091 added 'outputvar-collision' rule in the
      per-NODE-type-loop region; 093 added 'edge-no-data-dependency' in a sibling
      per-EDGE loop immediately after. Header comment + rule-union comment block
      identify both regions clearly. No conflicts; no overlapping edits.

      No tests added — PlaybookBuilder lacks test infrastructure (no test script in
      package.json, no jest/vitest deps). Future test infra would cover: (a) Node A
      (OutputVariable="foo") → Node B referencing {{foo.output.x}} → NO warning;
      (b) Node A → Node C without reference → warning fires on source nodeId;
      (c) snapshot of NodeValidationBadge showing the warning; (d) save allowed when
      only this warning is present.

      Files modified:
        - src/client/code-pages/PlaybookBuilder/src/services/canvasValidation.ts
          (rule union extension, per-edge loop call, validateEdgePerfHint function,
          header docstring update)
        - src/client/code-pages/PlaybookBuilder/src/types/canvas.ts
          (added warnings?: string[] to PlaybookNodeData)
        - src/client/code-pages/PlaybookBuilder/src/components/properties/NodePropertiesForm.tsx
          (wire warnings prop through to NodeValidationBadge)

      Build verify: tsc --noEmit on PlaybookBuilder produces ZERO errors in my edited
      files (5 webpack errors exist but are pre-existing module-resolution issues in
      Spaarke.UI.Components for @hello-pangea/dnd, pdfjs-dist, mammoth,
      @microsoft/applicationinsights-web, @spaarke/sdap-client — unrelated to 093).
    </completion-notes>
